Sentencas: NiO-Fe2O3/Gadolinium-doped CeO2 (GDC), NiO/GDC anode-supported fuel cells were compared at intermediate temperature to investigate the effect of ferrum (Fe) on anode microstructure and the cell performance.
Titulo: Effect of the adding ferrum in nickel/GDC anode-supported solid-oxide fuel cell in the intermediate temperature

Sentencas: The porosity of Fe2O3-containing anode tubes are 36.3% (those sintered at 1350 degrees C) and 31.8% (those sintered at 1400 degrees C), which are respectively 1.1% and 5.9% higher than that of the tubes without Fe2O3.
Titulo: Effect of the adding ferrum in nickel/GDC anode-supported solid-oxide fuel cell in the intermediate temperature

Sentencas: The effect of Fe on microstructure of anode has also been indicated by analyzing the volume fraction of the different-size pores.
Titulo: Effect of the adding ferrum in nickel/GDC anode-supported solid-oxide fuel cell in the intermediate temperature

Sentencas: At the operating temperature of 600 degrees C, the maximum power density increased nearly 100% using Fe-Ni (after reducing) bimetal anode.
Titulo: Effect of the adding ferrum in nickel/GDC anode-supported solid-oxide fuel cell in the intermediate temperature

Sentencas: From the impedance spectra, it is deduced that the improvement in power density is due to the decrease of overpotential resistance (low frequency part) related to gas transportation.
Titulo: Effect of the adding ferrum in nickel/GDC anode-supported solid-oxide fuel cell in the intermediate temperature
